Review_body:
Daniel Radcliffe as per usual is absolutely just fantastic in this movie. It's
an old school horror movie with no dumb double jumps, just a real good ol ghost story, one thing A
highly respected reviewer said that was Radcliffe didn't look old enough to have a young son but in those days they had kids when they were young so it it was believable to me. I saw this movie a few years ago but was distratced by stuff . Now I've watched it properly it a pure horror classic, Haven't done a spoiler but thought the ending was so clever. A definite 8;
